tic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Marie","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Maria .  When first introduced to England in the Middle Ages, it was Anglicized in pronunciation and respelled   Mary .  This French form was reintroduced into the English-speaking world as a separate name in the 19th century, and is still pronounced more or less in the French manner, although sometimes with the stress on the first syllable. It is now often used in combination with other names such as <i>Ellie</i>, <i>Chloe</i>, and <i>Lisa</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Marie de Preuilly was born in 1120, in Vendôme, Loir-et-Cher, France, her father, Geoffroy de PREUILLY IV dit Grisegonnelle, Count of Vendôme, was 40 and her mother, Mathilde de Châteaudun, was 41. She had at least 1 son with Seigneur Hamelin De Freteval. She died in 1182, in La Charité-sur-Loire, Cosne-Cours-sur-Loire, Nièvre, Burgundy, France, at the age of 62."},"et":{"1120–1182":"1120–1182","1105–Male":"1105–Surnud","1110–1182":"1110–1182","1120–1160":"1120–1160","1145–1188":"1145–1188","1080–1145":"1080–1145","1080–1130":"1080–1130","1080":"1080","25 September 1130":"25. september 1130","1105":"1105","1145":"1145","1188":"1188","1110":"1110","1120":"1120","1130":"1130","1160":"1160","1182":"1182","Casseneuil, Lot-Et-Garonne, Aquitaine, France":"Casseneuil, Lot-et-Garonne, Aquitaine, Prantsusmaa","Preuilly, Loir-et-Cher, Centre, France":"Loir-et-Cher, Centre, Prantsusmaa","Fréteval, Loir-et-Cher, Centre, France":"Fréteval, Loir-et-Cher, Prantsusmaa","St Gilles, Gard, Languedoc-Roussillon, Fra